div.p:
. . . Ambassador Davis is to talk to the
                    junta on Friday, September 21, to inform them of our goodwill, our intention to
                    recognize in the next few days, and about the delivery of medical supplies;

. . . a cable will be sent to Ambassador Davis telling him: of our intention to recognize and when; when
                    the emergency food supplies will be delivered; and authorizing the Ambassador to
                    discuss, with the junta, Chile’s middle-and long-term economic needs;
